CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 12, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes - Home Is Where Heart Remains - 'Goldies' House - Negroes are not alone in letting their property run down some time. The above house at Centre Ave. and Wandless St. is owned by a white woman, known as 'Goldie. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Three story brick house with turret on right, broken windows, overgrown yard, and light colored car parked in street on right, on Centre Avenue at intersection of Wandless Street, Hill District
